The paper deals with the application of deep learning technology to assess central serous chorioretinopathy (CSC) depicted on color fundus photographs. This involves image processing, normalization, and classification using the InceptionV3 deep learning architecture. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
